030/**
031 * Represents a mapping of {@link IMapKey} keys to values.
032 *
033 * @param <VALUE>
034 *          the value type
035 */
036public interface IMapItem<VALUE extends ICollectionValue>
037    extends IFunction, IItem, Map<IMapKey, VALUE>, IPrintable {
038  /**
039   * Get an empty, immutable map item.
040   *
041   * @param <V>
042   *          the value Java type
043   * @return an immutable map item
044   */
045  @NonNull
046  static <V extends ICollectionValue> IMapItem<V> empty() {
047    return AbstractMapItem.empty();
048  }
049
050  @Override
051  default QName getQName() {
052    return AbstractMapItem.QNAME;
053  }
054
055  @Override
056  default Set<FunctionProperty> getProperties() {
057    return AbstractMapItem.PROPERTIES;
058  }
059
060  @Override
061  default boolean isDeterministic() {
062    return true;
063  }
064
065  @Override
066  default boolean isContextDepenent() {
067    return false;
068  }
069
070  @Override
071  default boolean isFocusDepenent() {
072    return false;
073  }
074
075  @Override
076  default List<IArgument> getArguments() {
077    return AbstractMapItem.ARGUMENTS;
078  }
079
080  @Override
081  default int arity() {
082    return 1;
083  }
084
085  @Override
086  default boolean isArityUnbounded() {
087    return false;
088  }
089
090  @Override
091  default ISequenceType getResult() {
092    return AbstractMapItem.RESULT;
093  }
094
095  @Override
096  ISequence<?> execute(List<? extends ISequence<?>> arguments, DynamicContext dynamicContext, ISequence<?> focus);
097
098  @Override
099  default String toSignature() {
100    return "array()";
101  }
102
103  @Override
104  Map<IMapKey, VALUE> getValue();
105
106  @Override
107  default boolean hasValue() {
108    return true;
109  }
110
111  /**
112   * Determine if this sequence is empty.
113   *
114   * @return {@code true} if the sequence contains no items, or {@code false}
115   *         otherwise
116   */
117  @Override
118  default boolean isEmpty() {
119    return getValue().isEmpty();
120  }
121
122  /**
123   * Get the count of items in this sequence.
124   *
125   * @return the count of items
126   */
127  @Override
128  default int size() {
129    return getValue().size();
130
131  }
132
133  @Override
134  default ISequence<IMapItem<VALUE>> asSequence() {
135    return ISequence.of(this);
136  }
137
138  /**
139   * Get a new, immutable map item that contains the items in the provided map.
140   *
141   * @param <V>
142   *          the value Java type
143   * @param map
144   *          the map whose items are to be added to the new map
145   * @return a map item containing the specified entries
146   */
147  @NonNull
148  static <V extends ICollectionValue> IMapItem<V> ofCollection( // NOPMD - intentional
149      @NonNull Map<IMapKey, V> map) {
150    return map.isEmpty() ? empty() : new MapItemN<>(map);
151  }
152
153  /**
154   * Returns an unmodifiable map item containing zero mappings.
155   *
156   * @param <V>
157   *          the value Java type
158   * @return an empty {@code IMapItem}
159   */
160  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.ShortMethodName")
161  @NonNull
162  static <V extends ICollectionValue> IMapItem<V> of() {
163    return AbstractMapItem.empty();
164  }
165
166  /**
167   * Returns an unmodifiable map item containing a single mapping.
168   *
169   * @param <K>
170   *          the map item's key type
171   * @param <V>
172   *          the map item's value type
173   * @param k1
174   *          the mapping's key
175   * @param v1
176   *          the mapping's value
177   * @return a map item containing the specified mapping
178   * @throws NullPointerException
179   *           if the key or the value is {@code null}
180   */
181  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.ShortMethodName")
182  @NonNull
183  static <K extends IAnyAtomicItem, V extends ICollectionValue> IMapItem<V> of(@NonNull K k1, @NonNull V v1) {
184    return new MapItemN<>(entry(k1, v1));
185  }

187  /**
188   * Returns an unmodifiable map item containing two mappings.
189   *
190   * @param <K>
191   *          the map item's key type
192   * @param <V>
193   *          the map item's value type
194   * @param k1
195   *          the first mapping's key
196   * @param v1
197   *          the first mapping's value
198   * @param k2
199   *          the second mapping's key
200   * @param v2
201   *          the second mapping's value
202   * @return a map item containing the specified mappings
203   * @throws IllegalArgumentException
204   *           if the keys are duplicates
205   * @throws NullPointerException
206   *           if any key or value is {@code null}
207   */
208  @SuppressWarnings("PMD.ShortMethodName")
209  @NonNull
210  static <K extends IAnyAtomicItem, V extends ICollectionValue> IMapItem<V> of(
211      @NonNull K k1, @NonNull V v1,
212      @NonNull K k2, @NonNull V v2) {
213    return new MapItemN<>(
214        entry(k1, v1),
215        entry(k2, v2));
216  }

698  /**
699   * Returns an unmodifiable map item containing keys and values extracted from
700   * the given entries. The entries themselves are not stored in the map.
701   *
702   * @param <K>
703   *          the map item's key type
704   * @param <V>
705   *          the map item's value type
706   * @param entries
707   *          {@code Map.Entry}s containing the keys and values from which the map
708   *          is populated
709   * @return a map item containing the specified mappings
710   * @throws IllegalArgumentException
711   *           if there are any duplicate keys
712   * @throws NullPointerException
713   *           if any entry, key, or value is {@code null}, or if the
714   *           {@code entries} array is {@code null}
715   */
716  @SafeVarargs
717  @SuppressWarnings("varargs")
718  @NonNull
719  static <K extends IAnyAtomicItem, V extends ICollectionValue>
720      IMapItem<V> ofEntries(Map.Entry<IMapKey, ? extends V>... entries) {
721    return entries.length == 0 ? empty() : new MapItemN<>(entries);
722  }

724  /**
725   * Returns an unmodifiable {@link java.util.Map.Entry} containing the given key
726   * and value.
727   *
728   * @param <V>
729   *          the value's type
730   * @param key
731   *          the key
732   * @param value
733   *          the value
734   * @return an {@code Map.Entry} containing the specified key and value
735   * @throws NullPointerException
736   *           if the key or value is {@code null}
737   */
738  @NonNull
739  static <V extends ICollectionValue> Map.Entry<IMapKey, V> entry(@NonNull IAnyAtomicItem key, @NonNull V value) {
740    return entry(key.asMapKey(), value);
741  }
742
743  /**
744   * Returns an unmodifiable {@link java.util.Map.Entry} containing the given key
745   * and value.
746   *
747   * @param <V>
748   *          the value's type
749   * @param key
750   *          the key
751   * @param value
752   *          the value
753   * @return an {@code Map.Entry} containing the specified key and value
754   * @throws NullPointerException
755   *           if the key or value is {@code null}
756   */
757  @SuppressWarnings("null")
758  @NonNull
759  static <V extends ICollectionValue> Map.Entry<IMapKey, V> entry(@NonNull IMapKey key, @NonNull V value) {
760    return Map.entry(key, value);
761  }
762
763  /**
764   * Returns an unmodifiable Map item containing the entries of the given Map. The
765   * given Map must not be null, and it must not contain any null keys or values.
766   * If the given Map is subsequently modified, the returned Map will not reflect
767   * such modifications.
768   *
769   * @param <K>
770   *          the map item's key type
771   * @param <V>
772   *          the map item's value type
773   * @param map
774   *          a map item from which entries are drawn, must be non-null
775   * @return a map item containing the entries of the given {@code Map}
776   * @throws NullPointerException
777   *           if map is null, or if it contains any null keys or values
778   */
779  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
780  @NonNull
781  static <K extends IAnyAtomicItem, V extends ICollectionValue>
782      IMapItem<V> copyOf(Map<? extends IMapKey, ? extends V> map) {
783    return map instanceof IMapItem
784        ? (IMapItem<V>) map
785        : map.isEmpty()
786            ? empty()
787            : new MapItemN<>(new LinkedHashMap<>(map));
788  }
789
790  @Override
791  default void accept(IItemVisitor visitor) {
792    visitor.visit(this);
793  }
